---
description: Python quality and testing conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

## Quality bar

- Make small, localized changes; keep functions pure where possible.
- Prefer clear names and type hints when they add clarity.
- Avoid narrative/obvious comments.

## Testing

- After edits, run the smallest relevant test(s) when possible; otherwise run `uv run pytest`.

## Formatting/linting

- Respect the repo's settings in `pyproject.toml` (e.g., ruff line length 120).
